<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t18470614-1511">
               <interp inst="t18470614-1511" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/18470614"></interp>
               <interp inst="t18470614-1511" type="date" value="18470614"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t18470614-1511-charge-1" targOrder="Y" targets="def1-1511-18470614 t18470614-1511-offence-1 t18470614-1511-verdict-1"></join>
               <p>1511. <persName id="def1-1511-18470614" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-1511-18470614" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1511-18470614" type="age" value="32"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1511-18470614" type="surname" value="CHARLISH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1511-18470614" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JOHN CHARLISH</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18470614-1511-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18470614-1511-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="breakingPeace"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18470614-1511-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="wounding"></interp> for feloniously cutting and wounding <persName id="t18470614-name-1016" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18470614-name-1016" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470614-name-1016" type="surname" value="JARVIS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470614-name-1016" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18470614-1511-offence-1 t18470614-name-1016"></join>Edward Jarvis</persName> on the head, with intent to do him some grievous bodily harm.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. BALDWIN</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470614-name-1017" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470614-name-1017" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470614-name-1017" type="surname" value="JARVIS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470614-name-1017" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>EDWARD JARVIS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a smith and farrier, in the employ of Mr. Jones, in Great Leonard-street, Shoreditch. The prisoner worked there for about fourteen months—he left on the Saturday evening before Easter Sunday—he came to the shop on Monday, the 31st of May, about half-past six o'clock in the evening—I was working there—he had left some tools there—he came to fetch them away—I think he had some beer—he was there a quarter of an hour before I spoke to him—I was at work at the forge making a shoe for a gentleman—I was half an hour about it, and he kept on blackguarding me—I told him to be quite and hold his tongue—I had done that shoe and then I went to do another little job—he came up to me and, "Jarvis, you are a d—d thief, and a rogue"—I said, "If you call me that again, I will give you in charge"—I pushed him from me, and told him to go away, and come when Mr. Jones was at home—at that time he had got his tools in his apron, and he said, "You are Mr. Jones's foreman, look at what tools I have got"—I looked, and saw a hammer which did not belong to the prisoner—it had been there two years before he-came—he had put a handle in this ham<lb></lb>mer, and was going to take it away—I told him it was not his—he said, "If it is Mr. Jones's hammer, it is my handle, and I will saw it off"—some time after I went to put my hand to him to take the hammer, and I said, "You go away"—he said, "I will go when I like"—I went to put my hand to it and he took up the hammer and hit me twice on the head with it—I bled a great deal, and was taken to the surgeon—I was in bed from Monday till Thursday, and did not leave my room till Saturday—I had not struck the prisoner before I received those blows.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PARNELL</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> The prisoner was a little in drink when he came? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I do not know whether he was—I told him he was—I thought he was, by his appearance—I was thinking he was, but he told me he knew his own business—he did not speak to me for a quarter of an hour—he stood in the shop and spoke to the other men—the first thing he said to me was, that he was going to take his tools—I told him afterwards that I should fetch a police<lb></lb>man</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184706140182"></xptr>
               <p>if he did not go out—he said I might give him in charge if I liked, and I said I did not want to do anything of the sort if he went out quietly—he told me he would give me in charge if I hit him, but I did not—I did not say to him, "Will you <hi rend="italic">pull</hi> me if I hit you?"—I did not put my fist in his face, nor touch him at all—I did not pull his nose, nor threaten to pull it—I did not lay hold of the hammer that I know of—I tried to take it away—I might put my hand on it—I told him he should not take the hammer away—I put my hand on his shoulder and pushed him away—I told him he should not take the hammer without Mr. Jones was at home—I neither put my fist in his face, nor pulled his nose, nor threatened to pull it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">JURY</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did the prisoner work piece-work, or day-work? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Our work is all piece-work—the prisoner had done something to the hammer.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470614-name-1018" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470614-name-1018" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470614-name-1018" type="surname" value="DEAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470614-name-1018" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN DEAN</persName>
                  </hi>. I work at Mr. Jones's—I remember on the evening of the 31st May, the prisoner coming to the shop—Jarvis was there—I left the shop for about ten minutes, while the prisoner was there—when I came back Jarvis and the prisoner were wrangling—the prisoner was abusing Jarvis—I told him he had better come in the morning, when Mr. Jones was at home—I was about to leave the shop, I heard a noise, turned round and saw the prisoner strike Jarvis twice with the hammer—a man took the hammer from him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Who separated them after the blow was struck? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I cannot say—a man named Wren, was there—I heard Jarvis say, "Let me get at him"—I was not there during the whole time—I did not hear Jarvis threaten to pull his nose—I did not see him put his fist in his face—when I saw this scuffle, the hammer was up in the air—Jarvis had not got his hands on the prisoner's arm—I do not know where his hands were.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. BALDWIN</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Jarvis said, "Let me get at him?" <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—that was after the blows were struck.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470614-name-1019" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470614-name-1019" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470614-name-1019" type="surname" value="BEASLEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470614-name-1019" type="given" value="ANN"></interp>ANN BEASLEY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in Mr. Jones's service. On the evening of the 31st of May, I was on the stairs which look into the shop—the prisoner came for his tools—he had been there some time—I heard him ask Jarvis to look at his tools—Jarvis said he did not want anything to do with him, to go out of the shop—after he laid his tools down on his apron in the shop, Jarvis saw a hammer, he said it was his master's, and the prisoner should not take it away—the prisoner called Jarvis a d—d thief and a rouge—Jarvis told him to go out of the shop, he did not want anything to say to him—the prisoner came round to Jarvis, while Jarvis was at work by the fire, Jarvis turned round and said if he did not go he would pull his nose—he put his hand to his face, I did not see whether he pulled his nose—they were quarrelling for some time—I did not hear what they said—they walked down the shop as if they were going out of the gate—Jarvis put his hand on the prisoner's shoulder, and said he would take the hammer from him, he should not take it out of the shop—the prisoner turned round and struck him twice on the head with the hammer—I was frightened, and went away.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> It was when Jarvis told the prisoner he should not take the hammer away that the prisoner called him a rouge and a thief, was it not? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—after that, Jarvis told him if he did not go away he would pull his nose, and he put his fist in his face—I heard the prisoner say to him, "If you strike me I will have you up"—before these blows were struck, Jarvis put his hand on the prisoner's shoulder, and put his other hand before the prisoner, as though he were going to take the hammer from him—the prisoner swung round, and then I saw the hammer fall down on his head.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184706140183"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. BALDWIN</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Do you mean that it fell accidentally, or were they blows struck? <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> They were blows struck.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470614-name-1020" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470614-name-1020" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470614-name-1020" type="surname" value="BOYLAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470614-name-1020" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS BOYLAN</persName>
                  </hi>. I work at Mr. Jones. On the evening of the 31st of May, I was at the shop—the prisoner came for his tools—he fetched some of them, and put them in his apron—he asked for his hammer, and got hold of it—Jarvis said the hammer did not belong to him—he said it did, and they began to quarrel, and called one another rogues and thieves—Jarvis threatened to pull his nose if he did not go about his business—he said "I don't want to quarrel with you, stop till Mr. Jones comes," and he went to attend to a horse's foot that he was examining—I cannot tell whether he pulled the pri<lb></lb>soner's nose—I was standing with my back to the fire—Jarvis made a rush at the prisoner to take the hammer from him, and he struck him twice on the head with it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470614-name-1021" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470614-name-1021" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470614-name-1021" type="surname" value="GRANT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470614-name-1021" type="given" value="ALFRED HENRY"></interp>ALFRED HENRY GRANT</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable G</hi> 62.) I took the prisoner—I told him it was for wounding Jarvis—he asked me how he was—I said he was very dangerously ill—he said it was a very bad job; if Jarvis had not interfered with him he should not have done it—I produce the hammer.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470614-name-1022" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470614-name-1022" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470614-name-1022" type="surname" value="BOWER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470614-name-1022" type="given" value="ALFRED"></interp>ALFRED BOWER</persName>
                  </hi> I am a surgeon, and live in the Curtain-road. Jarvis was brought to my house on the evening of the 31st of May—he had two wounds on the scalp, and had lost a great deal of blood from them—they were narrow bruised wounds, about two inches long—they did not appear to be very deep—they were such as might be made by this hammer—I dressed them—they were not in themselves dangerous, but were calculated to produce erysipelas.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner received a good character.)</p>
               <p>
